{"履修期": "秋学期前半", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "This course is designed to provide students with a foundational understanding of business and economic data analysis. Students will learn key quantitative analysis tools, including measures of central tendency (mean, median, mode), measures of dispersion (variance, standard deviation), correlation, and regression analysis. In addition, the course will introduce financial data analysis techniques, such as ratio analysis, vertical and horizontal analysis, growth analysis, and bankruptcy prediction models. Through these tools, students will develop the ability to analyze, interpret, and apply economic and financial data for decision-making.", "到達目標": "Upon successful completion of the course, students will be able to apply basic statistical tools to summarize and analyze business and economic data, conduct regression analysis on economic and business data, perform financial statement analysis using ratios, vertical, and horizontal approaches, evaluate firm performance through growth analysis, use quantitative methods to assess the probability of firm bankruptcy, and integrate statistical and financial tools to draw evidence-based conclusions in business contexts.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "<span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Basic Accounting, Economics, Basic Finance</span></span></span></span></span></span>", "授業の概要・背景": "<span lang=\"EN-GB\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:;\">The course combines\nlectures, assigned readings, homework, and a final report to illustrate and\nreinforce concepts.</span>", "授業方法": "Face-to-face class. Students are required to follow the instructor's instructi